
=== DATABASE ===

Two different routes are possible, so you can either
start fresh (A) OR import the old bugs database (B).

==== (A) Starting fresh ====

  Create initial empty phpbugsdb:

    mysql -u root -p < phpbugsdb_create.sql
    mysql -u nobody phpbugsdb < bugs.sql

==== (B) Importing from old php-bugs-web ====

  Download and import a dump from this database:

    wget http://bugs.php.net/~rasmus/bugs-db-dump.sql.gz
    gunzip bugs-db-dump.sql.gz
    mysql -u nobody phpbugsdb < bugs-db-dump.sql

  Upgrade/convert to the new DB schema

    mysql -u nobody phpbugsdb < phpbugsdb_upgrade.sql

==== For either, add some additional data ====

  Checkout php-bugs-web code:

    svn co http://svn.php.net/repository/web/php-bugs/trunk php-bugs-web

  Convert bugtypes.inc into database entries:

    php -n convert_bugtypes_to_db.php

  Convert quick resolves into database entries:

    php -n convert_resolves_to_db.php

